Class TransitionRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • turing.TransitionRule

  • public class TransitionRule
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    Hunter R. Caskey Data structure containing the necessary information to model a transition rule in a Turing machine. These are corresponding to the five-tuple transitions described in the assignment specification.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TransitionRule

        public TransitionRule(int currentState,
                      char currentSymbol,
                      int newState,
                      char newSymbol,
                      int direction)
        Constructor for a transition rule in a Turing machine.
        Parameters:
        currentState - The state for which this rule applied to.
        currentSymbol - The symbol that must be under the read/write head of the TM for this rule to apply for.
        newState - The state to transition to granted that this rule should be enforced given the current state of the Turing machine.
        newSymbol - The symbol to write to the current cell under the read/write head of the Turing machine given that this rule should be enforced.
        direction - The direction to shift the tape of the Turing machine after performing a write operation.
